TEXT71: V1 and V2 were traveling south, V2 ahead of V1.V2 stopped for traffic.  V1
swerved to the right and the back of V2 was swiped by the front of V1.  V1
continued to curve to the right and the front of V1 struck a parked vehicle
(V3), which was facing west in a parking lot.  V3 was pushed forward and the
front of V3 struck the back of V4, which was also parked in the lot ahead of V3.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road. V2 was traveling in
the same direction ahead of V1 on the same roadway. V2 stopped to make a left
turn at a driveway. The back of V2 was contacted by the front of V1. V2 was
propelled partially into the northbound lane. Both vehicles came to final rest
in the roadway.
V1 traveling east when it lost control on snow/ice covered roadway and went off
the right side of the roadway.  V1 continued and struck a metal guardrail end
with its front.  V1 continued up the guardrail and rolled over 3/4 turns to the
right down a small embankment and came to rest facing east on its left side.
V1 was traveling south approaching an intersection intending to turn left.  V3
was behind V1 traveling in the same direction.  V2 was traveling north
approaching the same intersection.  V1's right side and the front of V2
impacted.  V2 continued through the intersection, crossed the centerline and
contacted V3 in the left side with its front.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north negotiating a left curve on an upgrade.  V1 went
off the right side of the road into a drainage ditch.  The front left of vehicle
1 struck the far side of the ditch.  V1 rotated clockwise and the undercarriage
then scraped the top of a concrete culvert headwall.  V1 continued to rotate
clockwise and overturned on to it's left side.  V1 came to rest off the right
side of the road on its left side.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south negotiating a sharp left curve on an upgrade.  The
driver lost control due to sand and salt on the roadway.  V1 went off the right
side of the road.  The front of V1 struck a 9 cm diameter tree, which uprooted
the tree.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road. V1 went off the
right side of the road.  The front of vehicle 1 struck the down turned end of a
guardrail. The vehicle mounted the guardrail and continued to travel north.  The
vehicle crossed a stream, dismounted the guardrail and the left side of the
vehicle swiped the guardrail.  The front of V1 struck the ground and the vehicle
continued to travel northbound. The front of V1 swiped a 36 cm diameter tree.
V1 then veered to the left until itstruck a 10 by 10 cm mailbox post. V1 came to
final rest partially back on the roadway facing northwest.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north.  Vehicle 2 was traveling north ahead of V1.  V2
decelerated to make a right turn at a business driveway.  The back of V2 and the
front of V1 contacted.
V1 was traveling north negotiating a left curve.  V1 lost control and went off
the right side of the roadway striking a delineator with its left side.  V1
continued and struck a 33 cm diameter pole with its left side and came to rest
facing in an easterly direction.
V1 was traveling south on a level two-lane undivided roadway.  V1 crossed the
centerline, went off the left side of the roadway and struck two valve box
risers for a fire hydrant with its front.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north on an undivided two-way, two-lane roadway.
Vehicle #1 departed roadway on the east side and impacted a 25cm tree with the
frontal end plane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve on an upgrade.  The vehicle started to slide and the driver overcorrected.
The vehicle went off the right side of the road.  The front of V1 struck a 21
cm diameter tree, uprooting the tree.  The vehicle then overturned to the right.
During the roll, the right side of the vehicle struck a clump of small trees.
The vehicle continued to overturn and the right side of the vehicle swiped a 23
cm diameter tree.  The vehicle came to rest off the right side of the road
leaning against the clump of trees and the 23 cm diameter tree.  It was raining,
the road was snow/ice covered, and it was daylight at the time of the crash.
The frontal air bags deployed.
V1 was traveling west.  A deer entered the roadway and V1 steered right to avoid
same.  V1 went off the right side of the road into a parking area and struck a
large cement block with its front.  V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to
rest.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided four-lane road negotiating a left
curve in the left lane.  V2 was traveling north on the same road negotiating the
right curve in the right lane. V1 rotated counterclockwise and the right side
of V1 and the front of V2 impacted.
V1 was traveling southeasterly on a two-lane roadway that curved to the right.
V1 decelerated and swerved to the right to avoid a deer in the roadway. V1
departed the right side of the roadway and contacted a 34 cm diameter tree with
its front end-plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane, two-way roadway which
was covered with ice and snow.  Vehicle #1 lost traction and departed the
roadway on the right side and impacted a tree with the frontal end plane.
Vehicle towed due to front axle damage.
V1 was traveling east.  V1 went off the right side of the roadway and began to
rotate clockwise.  V1 continued to rotate and struck a 52 cm diameter tree with
its left side.  V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing in a
southeasterly direction.  It was snowing, the roadway snow/ice covered and it
was dark at the time of the crash.  V1 was towed due to damage.  Operator V1 was
transported, treated and hospitalized due to injuries.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a slight
right curve.  V1 started to rotate and went off the right side of the road.
The vehicle dropped off the edge of the pavement and the front of the vehicle
struck a mound of earth.  The vehicle deflected to the right slightly and the
left side of the vehicle struck a 28 by 31 cm diameter tree.  V1 came to rest
off the right side of the road.
Vehicle 1, a school bus, was traveling north on an undivided two- lane road
approaching a four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east on the undivided
two-lane road, negotiating a left curve on an upgrade.  The front of V1
contacted the right side of V2. V2 was rotated clockwise and the left side of V2
struck a small embankment on the northeast corner of the intersection. V2
continued back into the roadway and came to final rest.
V1 was traveling west.  V2 traveling south. V1 was struck on the right side by
the front of V2.  V1 was rotated clockwise off the southwest corner of the
intersection, struck a sign post with its right side and came to rest facing in
a southeasterly direction.  V2 continued off the side of the road and came to
rest facing south.  It was snowing, the roadway snow/ice covered and it was dusk
at the time of the crash.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on an undivided two-way, two-lane roadway.
Vehicle #1 started to rotate counterclockwise due to snow and ice on the roadway
.  Vehicle #1 then departed the roadway on the right side and impacted a 34cm
pole with the right side plane.
V1 was traveling south on a level two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve
to the left.  V1 drove off the right side of the roadway and struck two 4 x 4
mailbox posts with its front end-plane.  A broken section of post flew up and
struck the roof.  V1 continued and struck the mailbox post with its right side.
V1 continued off the road, struck a 32 cm tree with its front and came to rest
facing south.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a snow and ice covered roadway negotiating a
left curve on a downgrade.  V1 rotated clockwise and the vehicle went off the
right side of the road.  The left side of V1 struck a 33 cm diameter utility
pole.  The vehicle continued to rotate clockwise and came to rest partially in
the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane road.  A deer entered the
roadway.  V1 went off the left side of the road.  The vehicle climbed an
embankment and continued off the left side of the road.  The vehicle crossed an
intersecting roadway and continued to travel east.  The vehicle went into a
wooded area and the front of the vehicle struck a 17 cm diameter tree.  The tree
was uprooted and pushed eastward.  The front of V1 then struck a 9 cm diameter
tree. The vehicle continued east rotated counterclockwise slightly and the
undercarriage struck an embankment.  The vehicle went up the embankment a short
distance and the front of the vehicle struck an 8 cm diameter tree.  The vehicle
started to overturn. During the roll, the right side of the vehicle struck an
11 cm diameter tree.  V1 continued to roll and then struck an 11 cm diameter
tree with the undercarriage and came to rest off the left side of the road on it
wheels.
V1 traveling south on a level two lane undivided roadway approaching a four-leg
intersection.  V2 traveling north on the same roadway approaching the same
intersection.  V1 enters the intersection to turn left.  V1 strikes the front of
V2 with its front.  V1 rotates clockwise off the northeasterly corner of the
intersection and strikes a sign post with it back and comes to rest facing
south.  V2 continues a short distance and comes to rest facing in a northerly
direciton.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve and approaching an intersection controlled by a stop sign for V1.  Vehicle
2 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left curve and
approaching the same intersection as V1.  V1 attempted to turn left at the
intersection.  The front of V2 contacted the front of V1.  V1 rotated
counterclockwise slightly and the right side of V2 was struck by the front of
V1.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway and were towed due to damage.
The right front seat passenger in V2 was air lifted to a trauma center due to
injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was dry and it was daylight at the
time of the crash.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway.  V1 went off the right
side of the roadway and struck a 4 x 4 mailbox post with its front.  The post
snapped and struck the hood of V1.  V1 continued off the roadway and struck a
small bush with its front.  V1 then struck a 20 cm diameter pole with its front,
snapped same and the top portion of the pole struck the hood of V1.  V1
continued, went off a small embankment and struck a drainage grate with its
right rear tire coming to rest facing south on an intersecting roadway.
Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling north on an undivided two-lane road
negotiating a slight right curve with V2 in front of V1.  V2 slowed to make a
right turn at a driveway. The back of V2 was impacted by the front of V1.  V2
rotated clockwise and traveled off the northeast corner of the intersecting
driveway.  The left front tire on V2 struck a curb on the northeast corner of
the intersecting driveway and the vehicle continued to travel off the right side
of the road.  The front of V2 then struck a snow bank.  V2 continued to travel
off the right side of the road and the front of V2 swiped the left side of V3, a
vehicle parked in a parking lot facing west.
V1 was traveling north negotiating a curve to the left.  Two deer enter the
roadway.  Operator V1 brakes and steers right to avoid a collision.  V1
continues off the right side of the road striking a snow embankment with its
front.  V1 continues down an embankment striking rocks with its undercarriage.
V1 strikes a tree with its left side and comes to rest facing in a northeasterly
direction.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve on a downgrade.  Vehicle 2 (a medium-heavy truck) was traveling south on
the same undivided two-lane road negotiating a right curve on an upgrade.  V1
crossed into the southbound lanes.  V2 moved to the right.  The front of V2 was
struck by the front of V1.  V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest in the
roadway facing southeast.  V2 continued to travel south and the front of V2
struck a rural mailbox.  V2 came to rest off the right side of the road.  Both
vehicles were towed due to damage.  The driver of V1 was transported to a trauma
center where he was hospitalized.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a level two lane undivided roadway.  V1 was
behind V2.  V1's front and V2's back impacted. V2 went off the left side of the
roadway and rolled over 4 quarter turns.  V1 continued off the left side of the
roadway, up a small embankment and struck a 28 cm tree and a 33 cm tree with its
front, rotated slightly counterclockwise and came to rest facing in a
southwesterly direction.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a sharp
left curve.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The front of the vehicle
struck a stone wall.  V1 rotated clockwise and continued across a driveway.  The
left side of the vehicle then struck the corner of a stone and concrete wall.
The vehicle continued to rotate clockwise and the left side struck the wall a
second time.  The vehicle came to rest off the right side of the road facing
southeast.  V1 was towed due to damage.  The driver was transported due to
injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was wet and sand covered and it was
daylight at the time of the crash.  No air bags deployed.
V1 was traveling west on a level two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve
to the right.  V1 went off the left side of the roadway and struck a 4 cm
sapling, a 20 cm tree and then a 30 cm diameter tree with its front.  V1 rotated
counterclockwise back onto the roadway and came to rest facing in a westerly
direction on the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east.  V2 was stopped in traffic facing east on the same
road, ahead of V1, waiting to turn left at an intersection.  The front of V1
contacted the back of V2.  V2 was propelled forward and to the right and came to
rest at the right edge of the roadway.  V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to
rest partially in the westbound lane.  V3 was traveling west.  V3 observed V1
crossing into his lane and swerved to the right.  Debris from the impact of V1
and V2 struck V3 on the left side.
V1 traveling west on a level two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to
the right.  V1 went off the left side of the roadway and began to rotate
slightly clockwise.  V1 struck a 20 cm tree with its front and then a 28 cm
diameter pole with its left side.  V1 then struck the uprooted tree roots with
its front.  V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing in a easterly
direction.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve on an upgrade.  V2 was traveling south on the same undivided two-lane road
negotiating a left curve on a downgrade.  V1 moved to the left and entered the
northbound lane.  The front of V1 struck the left side of V2. V1 was rotated
counterclockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing southwest. V2 came to
rest in the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve and approaching an intersection.  V1 went off the right side of the road,
rotated counterclockwise slightly and the right side of the vehicle swiped a 5
cm diameter tree.  The vehicle continued off the right side of the road and the
front of the vehicle struck a 200 cm high wooden stockade fence.  The vehicle
went through the fence and the front of the vehicle struck a 19 cm diameter
tree.  V1 came to rest off the right side of the road.  V1 was towed due to
damage.  The driver was transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear, the
road was dry, it was dark and the road was lighted at the time of the crash.
V1 and V2 traveling on a level two lane undivided roadway.  V2 was behind V1.
V1 stops behind an uninvolved vehicle and is struck in the rear by the front of
V2.  It was cloudy, the roadway dry and it was daylight at the time of the
crash.  V2 was towed due to damage.  There were no reported injuries.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a sharp
left curve on an upgrade.  Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same undivided
two-lane road negotiating a sharp right curve on an upgrade.  V1 crested the
grade and started on the downgrade.  V2 moved to the left into the southbound
lane. The driver of V1 observed V2 and moved V1 to the right edge of the
roadway.  The front of V1 struck the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in
the roadway.  Both vehicles were towed due to damage. The driver of V2 was
transported due to injuries.  It was snowing, the road was snow/ice covered and
it was daylight at the time of the crash.  The frontal air bags in both vehicles
deployed.
V1 traveling north on a level two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to
the right.  V1 went off the right side of the roadway and struck a 23 cm
diameter pole with its front.  V1 continued and struck the ground with its front
coming to rest facing in a northerly direction.  The weather was clear, the
roadway dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.  V1 was towed due to
damage.  Operator of V1 was transported to a medical facility, treated and
released.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to the
left.  V1 went off the right side of the roadway and began to rotate
counterclockwise.  V1 continued off the roadway and struck a metal guardrail
with its front.  V1 continued along the metal guardrail and struck it again with
its front.  V1 came to rest facing east.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a sharp
left curve on a downgrade.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The front
of V1 went into a deep ditch.  V1 came to rest in the ditch.  V1 was towed due
to damage.  The driver was transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear,
the road was dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.  No air bags
deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve.  The vehicle crossed into the westbound lane. The driver swerved to the
right and the vehicle started to rotate clockwise.  V1 went off the right side
of the road and continued to rotate clockwise.  The left side of the vehicle
struck a 26 cm diameter utility pole.  The vehicle came to rest off the right
side of the road.  The vehicle was towed due to damage.  The three occupants of
the vehicle were transported due to possible injuries and were treated and
released from a trauma center.  It was raining, the road was wet and it was dark
and the road was lighted at the time of the crash.  No air bags deployed.
V1 traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway on an upgrade.  V2 traveling
north on the same roadway on a downgrade approaching a driveway to the left.  V2
turns left into the driveway and is contacted on the right side by the front of
V1.  V2 is rotated clockwise and comes to final rest facing in a northwesterly
direction.  V1 comes to final rest facing south.
V1 traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve, to the
left.  V1 drove off the right side of the roadway and began to rotate slightly
counterclockwise.  V1 continued off the roadway, into a deep ditch and rolled
over onto its right side coming to rest facing west.
V1 traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to the
left.  V1 drives off the right side of the roadway striking a metal guardrail
with its front.  V1 corrects to the left, back onto the roadway crossing both
lanes.  V1 corrects back to the right, goes off the right side of the roadway
and strikes the guardrail with its front.  V1 continues along the guardrail and
comes to rest facing north.  It was cloudy, the roadway dry and it was daylight
at the time of the crash.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided three-lane road negotiating a
slight left curve on a downgrade and approaching an intersecting roadway to the
right.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the intersecting roadway and approaching
the same intersection as V1.  V2 attempted to make a left turn at the
intersection.  The left side of V2 was struck by  the front of V1.  V1 was
rotated counterclockwise and went off the west side of the roadway where it came
to final rest.  V2 rotated clockwise and went off the west side of the roadway
where it came to final rest.
Vehicle 1, an unmarked police car, was traveling south on an undivided two-lane
road with an emergency light activated and approaching an intersection
controlled by a stop sign for V1.  V2, a tractor-trailer, was traveling east on
an undivided two-lane road on a downgrade and approaching the same intersection
as V1.  V1 attempted to cross the intersection. The right side of V1 was struck
by the front of V2.  V1 was rotated clockwise and went off the south east corner
of the intersection.  The left side of V1 struck a short chain link fence and
came to final rest off the roadway.  V2 came to final rest in the roadway.
V1 traveling south.  V2 traveling east.  V1 is contacted in the right side by
the front of V2.  V1 is rotated clockwise off the southeast corner of the
intersection and struck a traffic control pole with its left side.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided four-lane road negotiating a slight
right curve in the right lane.  A deer ran into the roadway from the left side
of the road into the path of V1.  The front of V1 struck the deer.  The vehicle
came to rest in the roadway.  V1 was towed due to damage.  No occupants of the
vehicle were transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was
dry, it was dark and the road was not lighted at the time of the crash.  The
driver air bag deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane road approaching an
intersection controlled by a stop sign and red flashing traffic signal for V1.
V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two-lane roadway and approaching the
same intersection as V1 which was controlled by a flashing amber traffic signal
for V2.  The driver of V1 attempted to turn left at the intersection.  V1
entered the intersection and the left side of V1 was contacted by the front of
V2. Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.
V1 traveling north.  V1 drove off the left side of the roadway and struck a
fence with its front.  V1 continued and struck a 38 cm diameter tree with its
front.
V1 traveling on a two lane undivided roadway on an upgrade.  A deer enters the
roadway from the right and is struck by the front of V1.  The weather was clear,
the roadway dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.  V1 was towed due
to damage.  There were no reported injuries.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road.  Vehicle 2 was
traveling south on the same undivided two-lane road.  Vehicle 1 crossed into the
southbound lane and went off the left side of the road.  The front of V1 swiped
a metal guardrail.  V1 continued along the guardrail and started to return to
the roadway.  The front of vehicle 1 struck the left side of V2.  V2 was rotated
counterclockwise and went off the roadway into a dirt parking lot.  V1
continued to travel along the west shoulder and came to rest on the west
shoulder. Both vehicles were towed due to damage.
V1 traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to the
right.  V2 traveling west on the same roadway negotiating the curve to the left.
V2 crossed into the eastbound lane and contacted V1 in the right side with its
front.  V2 rotated clockwise and rolled over, two quarter turns, onto its roof.
V1 came to final rest facing east in the westbound lane.  V2 came to final
rest on its roof facing west in the eastbound lane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve.  V2 was traveling south on the same undivided two-lane road negotiating
the left curve.  V1 attempted to make a left turn into a driveway.  The right
side of V1 was struck by the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the
roadway.  V1 was towed due to damage.  No occupants of either vehicle were
transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was dry and it was
daylight at the time of the crash.  No air bags deployed in either vehicle.
V1 traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to the
right.  V1 went off the right side of the roadway rotating clockwise and struck
a 17cm tree with its left side.  V1 continued to rotate clockwise and struck an
embankment with its left side.  V1 came to rest facing in a northwesterly
direction.  The weather was cloudy, the roadway wet and it was dark and
unlighted at the time of the crash.  V1 was towed due to damage.  Operator of V1
was transported, treated and released at a local hospital.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east negotiating a steep downgrade on an undivided
two-lane road and approaching an intersection controlled by a stop sign for V1.
V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two-lane roadway, negotiating a left
curve on a downgrade and approaching the same intersection as V1.  V1 attempted
to make a left turn at the intersection.  The left side of V1 was struck by the
front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.  Both vehicles were
towed due to damage.  No occupants of either vehicle were transported due to
injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was dry and it was daylight at the
time of the crash.  No air bags deployed in either vehicle.
V1 traveling south on a 3 lane undivided roadway which was under construction.
V1 went off the right side of the roadway striking 12 cm high curb with its
front.  V1 continued and struck a mailbox with its front.  A portion of the
mailbox became dislodged and struck the hood of V1. V1 continued and struck the
curb with its front. V1 came to rest facing in a southerly direction.  The
weather was clear, the roadway dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.
V1 was towed due to damage.  There were no reported injuries.
V1 traveling east on a two-lane undivided roadway approaching a four-leg
intersection.  V2, a police car with lights and siren activated, was traveling
north on a two-lane undivided cross street controlled by a stop sign.  V3 was
traveling on the two-lane undivided cross street and was stopped at the
intersection.  V2 pulled alongside V3 at the intersection.  A non-contact
vehicle crossed into V1's lane.  V1 veered right to avoid the non-contact
vehicle, went off the right side of the intersection and struck V2 in the left
side with its front.  V2 was pushed into V3 striking it in the left side with
its right side.  V2 and V3 came to rest facing in a northerly direction.  V1
came to rest facing in a easterly direction.
Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling north on an undivided two lane road with
vehicle 1 ahead of V2.  V1 slowed to make a left turn into a driveway.  As V1
was making the left turn, V2 moved into the southbound lane of travel.  The left
side of V1 was struck by the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the
roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane road negotiating the left
curve portion of an "S" curve on a steep downgrade.  Vehicle 1 went slightly off
the right side of the road.  The right front wheel swiped a large rock and then
impacted a large rock causing damage to the wheel and axle.  The vehicle came
back into the roadway and to final rest  facing northeast. V1 was towed due to
damage.  No injuries were reported. It was raining, the road was wet and it was
daylight at the time of the crash.  No air bags deployed in the vehicle.
Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling north on an undivided two-lane road
negotiating a slight right curve on a downgrade with vehicle 2 ahead of V1.  V2
decelerated to make a left turn at an intersecting roadway.  The back of V2 was
contacted by the front of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest, on the roadway.
V1 traveling east on a two-lane undivided roadway.  V1 attempted to avoid a
non-contact vehicle, drove off the right side of the roadway and struck a parked
vehicle in the back with its front.  The weather was clear, the roadway dry and
it was daylight at the time of the crash.  V1 was towed due to damage.  There
were no reported injuries.
V1 traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to the
left.  V1 went off the right side of the roadway and struck a w-beam guardrail
with its front.  V1 continued along the guardrail and came back on the roadway
V1 crossed both lanes, went off the left side of the roadway, down an embankment
and came to rest facing northwestery in a small marshy area.  It was raining,
the roadway wet and it was daylight at the time of the crash.  V1 was towed due
to damage.  There were no reported injuries.
Vehicle 1 (a school bus) was stopped at a traffic signal at a "T" shaped
intersection facing south on an undivided two-lane road which was curved to the
right.  V2 was traveling west negotiating a left curve on an undivided two-lane
road and approaching the same intersection as V1 which was also controlled by a
traffic signal for V2.  V2 made a right turn at the intersection.  The front of
V2 struck the front of V1.
V1 traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway.  V1 drove off the right side
of the road and struck a 48 cm diameter tree with its front.  V1 rotated
clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing in a westerly direction.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve on a downgrade.  V1 went off the right side of the road into a drainage
ditch.  The vehicle's  right front wheel struck a metal culvert grate, and the
front of the vehicle struck the ground.  The vehicle then continued across a
driveway and the undercarriage struck the ground two more times.  The vehicle

This single vehicle crash took place on a two-lane, asphalt-constructed, rural
highway.  In the area of the crash, the roadway was downhill and curving right
for eastbound travel.  At the time of the crash, it was daylight and there were
no adverse weather or roadway conditions.    V1 was eastbound on a 2-lane rural
highway when a right front tie rod end apparently became detached, and V1
departed the road to the right into a shallow ditch, contacted a bush with the
front plane, climbed an embankment and rolled left onto its left side.  V1 came
to rest on its left side, facing eastbound.
V1 was eastbound in the number one right turn lane intending to turn right and
exit a divided state highway consisting of 2 eastbound through lanes one left
turn only and one right turn only lane and two westbound lanes.   V1 had a wheel
impact with the right front wheel as it departed the road to the right, then
crossed over the sidewalk and had a frontal event with a metal fence rail.
This two-vehicle crash took place on a three-lane, asphalt-constructed, rural
highway with a two-way center left turn lane.  At the time of the crash, it was
overcast and dusk.  In the area of the crash, the highway was straight and
level, and there were two business driveways on the westbound road edge.    V1
was westbound, behind V2 when V2 slowed to turn right into a business and the
front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.  After impact, V1 came to rest
in the westbound traffic lane and V2 came to rest diagonally across the
business drive, facing northwest.
This two-vehicle crash took place at a "T" intersection of two secondary roads.
the north-south oriented roadway was uncontrolled and the eastbound roadway was
controlled by a stop sign.   V1 was eastbound, at the stop sign intending to
turn right and V2 was southbound, intending to go straight.  The V1 driver
entered the intersection, noticed V2 and accelerated on a heading straight
across the roadway toward a driveway. The front of V2 and the left plane of V1
collided in the intersection.  After impact, V2 came to rest on the east side of
the northbound lane, facing south and V1 came to rest in the driveway facing
east.
This two-vehicle crash took place on a five-lane, asphalt-constructed highway
with a raised concrete median and left-turn bays at intersections with driveways
and cross streets.  This highway is intersected from the south by a three-lane,
asphalt-constructed secondary roadway with a left turn bay, which is controlled

V1 was eastbound negotiating a curve right when its front-end plane contacted a

V1 was northbound negotiating a curve right on a wet, rural, two-lane highway

This crash took place on a two-lane, asphalt-constructed rural roadway. V1 was
southbound on the southbound shoulder and entered the road intending to make a

V1 was southbound in the #1 lane of a divided highway with two southbound lanes

one lane on its wheels facing generally northwest.
V1 was northbound in the #2 lane of a rural divided highway with 2 lanes in each

V1 was southbound on a wet two-lane rural highway, lost traction, departed the

This two-vehicle crash occurred on a straight, uphill 3-lane asphalt roadway.
The crash occurred during darkness with heavy snow on the roadway.    Vehicle #1

This two-vehicle crash took place on a north-south, five-lane,

This two-vehicle crash occurred on a 5-lane asphalt roadway in a business and

V1 was southbound in the number one lane of a wet divided highway with two

This single vehicle crash took place on a two-lane, asphalt-constructed, rural

This two-vehicle crash took place on a two-lane, asphalt-constructed, rural
secondary roadway near a "T" intersection with another two-lane,

V1 entered a 4-way intersection northbound after stopping at the stop sign and

westbound traffic.  Both vehicles intended to go straight.  The V1 left side
plane and V2 front plane collided in the intersectionwhich was eastbound.  After

intersection.
V1 turned left at a residential T-intersection, stopped, then backed up
intending to turn around and proceed in the opposite direction.  The back of V1
impacted and went up and over a short rock wall then came to rest.
This single vehicle crash took place on a two-lane, asphalt-constructed rural
secondary roadway.  In the area of the crash, the roadway was wet, straight and

This two-vehicle crash took place on a four-lane, asphalt-constructed, east-west
oriented highway with a raised concrete center median.  In the area of the

V1 was northbound on a two-way three lane road approaching a controlled
intersection intending to go straight and V2 was westbound in the number one
lane of a five-lane highway approaching the same intersection, also intending to
go straight. The two vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2
contacted the left side of V1.
V1 was northbound, stopped at a stop sign, then entered a four-way intersection
intending to go straight.  V2 was westbound in the number two lane, negotiating
a gradual curve left, approaching the same intersection not controlled for
westbound traffic.  The two vehicles entered the intersection and the front of
V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was southbound in the number two lane and V2 was northbound stopped in the
center turn lane of a five-lane roadway intending to turn left onto a side

Head-on.
V1 was southbound in the number two lane and V2 was southbound in the number one
lane.  V2 drifted into the number one lane and the right side of V1 impacted
the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling southbound around a leftward curve.  V1 departed the road to
the left side, where its front impacted an embankment. V1 deflected right and

V1 was westbound when an elk entered the roadway and contacted the front plane

V1 was northbound in the number two lane of a divided highway with two
northbound lanes and departed the left road edge, was steered right, entered a
clockwise rotation, departed the road to the right and contacted a steep,

V1 was westbound on a two lane rural highway negotiating a gradual uphill curve
right and impacted a large rock in the roadway with the undercarriage.  The rock

This 2-vehicle crash occurred in a rural area with various curves and elevations

Vehicle #1 was northbound when, as the driver stated, vehicles were stopped

V1 was northbound, drifted to the right and the front plane contacted the back

V1 was westbound when it departed the right road edge, was steered left and

This single vehicle crash took place on a two-lane, asphalt-constructed, rural

V1 was northbound in the #1 lane when it departed the right road edge.  V1

This single vehicle crash took place on an asphalt-constructed, east to west

westbound when the vehicle rotated clockwise and departed the right road edge.
V1 tripped and rolled left 2-quarter turns, coming to rest on its roof facing
east.
This single-vehicle crash occurred on 4-lane divided asphalt roadway with an

Vehicle #1 was eastbound in the number two lane of a five lane roadway

This single-vehicle crash occurred in a rural area on a 2-lane asphalt roadway.

This two-vehicle crash took place on a five-lane, asphalt-constructed urban

Vehicle #1 was southbound in the #1 lane when it departed the right road edge

V1 was exiting a business located on the south side of the highway, turning left

V1 was westbound on a two-lane rural highway negotiating a gradual curve to the

This single vehicle crash took place on a four-lane, asphalt-constructed, rural

V1 was traveling northbound and approaching and intersection to turn left.  V2

As V1 turned, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.
Vehicle #1 was eastbound in the #1 lane of a five lane urban roadway when it's

V1 was traveling eastbound on a five-lane roadway and about to turn left into a

V1 was northbound when it departed the right road edge and the right side struck

V1 was southbound and V2 was eastbound when the front plane of V1 contacted the

This two-vehicle crash took place at the intersection of two, two-lane,

This 2- vehicle crash occurred at the intersection of a 6-lane asphalt roadway

Vehicle #2 was eastbound attempting to go straight.  In the intersection the

This two-vehicle crash took place on a five-lane, asphalt-constructed highway

V1 was southbound crossing a four-leg intersection.  V2 was eastbound crossing

V1 was eastbound in lane two of a five-lane roadway approaching a traffic

The front of V1 struck the back of V2.
Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two-lane roadway turning left at an intersection.
V2 was westbound crossing over the intersection.  The front of V1 struck the
front of V2.
V1 was exiting a private business drive and turning left into westbound traffic

This single vehicle crash took place on a two-lane, dirt, forest service road.

Vehicle #1 was westbound in the #1 lane of a rural highway with two lanes in

V1 was northbound in the number two lane and the V1 driver applied the brakes.

Vehicle #1 entered the road from a private drive intending to turn left and it's

This two-vehicle crash took place on an east-west oriented, five-lane,

V1 was traveling west on a rural three-lane highway consisting of two westbound

This two-vehicle crash took place on a five-lane, asphalt-constructed, east-west

This single-vehicle crash occurred in a rural area with various curves and

This single vehicle crash occurred in a rural area on a 2-lane asphalt roadway.

Vehicle #1 was eastbound in the #1 lane then went left and entered the oncoming

This single vehicle crash took place on a narrow, winding U.S. Forest Service
